                ('Apply De Morgan\'s Law to: !(x > 0 && y > 0)', ['!(A && B) = !A || !B', '= !(x > 0) || !(y > 0)', '= (x <= 0) || (y <= 0)', 'This is true when at least one of x or y is not positive']),
                ('Is String comparison with == reliable?', ['No — == compares references (memory addresses) for objects', 'Two Strings with same characters may not be the same object', 'Always use .equals() for String content comparison', 'AP® exam frequently tests this distinction']),
